docs.abstract: Small and midsize firms are increasingly steering clear of going public, giving big companies outsize influence over stock markets and hampering business creation, wage growth and productivity.
docs.snippet: Small and midsize firms are increasingly steering clear of going public, giving big companies outsize influence over stock markets and hampering business creation, wage growth and productivity.
docs.lead_paragraph: Ryan Smith spent years planning to sell shares of his software company, Qualtrics, on the stock market, meeting with bankers, carefully auditing financials and shaping a Wall Street-friendly narrative about the company’s prospects. Two weeks ago, the finish line was close, with a listing on the Nasdaq just a few days away.

headline.main: More Small Companies Avoid I.P.O.s, Sapping U.S. Economy’s Vitality
headline.print_headline: A Lucrative Thing Happened on the Way to Wall St.

byline.original: By Erin Griffith and Matt Phillips

docs.abstract: Coming into these I.P.O.s, there were many questions about whether investors were willing to swallow the risk of the latest crop of tech companies.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The rush of so-called unicorn start-ups toward the public markets had a rocky start. But Thursday indicated that investors remain eager to get a piece of them.

docs.abstract: The workplace messaging company, one of the technology industry’s so-called unicorns, said Monday it had confidentially filed to go public.
docs.snippet: The workplace messaging company, one of the technology industry’s so-called unicorns, said Monday it had confidentially filed to go public.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Slack, a workplace messaging company, said Monday that it had confidentially filed paperwork for an initial public offering, joining the growing number of technology start-ups heading to the stock market.

headline.main: Slack Files for Public Offering, Joining Silicon Valley’s Stock Market Rush
headline.print_headline: Slack Quietly Joins the Stampede Of Start-Ups Bound for the Market

docs.abstract: Following the money isn’t easy in the opaque world of venture capital.
docs.snippet: Following the money isn’t easy in the opaque world of venture capital.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — When John Vrionis and Jyoti Bansal set out to raise money this year for their first venture capital fund, Unusual Ventures, industry peers advised them to go after the easy money — sovereign wealth funds like those managed by Saudi Arabia and Abu Dhabi, which have become major investors in Silicon Valley.

headline.main: Start-Ups Ask, ‘Are We Making Money for Saudi Arabia?’
headline.print_headline: Suddenly Questioning Easy Money For Start-Ups

docs.abstract: Mark Zuckerberg’s charity is teaming up with groups like the Ford Foundation to spend half a billion dollars on housing around San Francisco.
docs.snippet: Mark Zuckerberg’s charity is teaming up with groups like the Ford Foundation to spend half a billion dollars on housing around San Francisco.
docs.lead_paragraph: A group of San Francisco Bay Area philanthropists has pledged to spend half a billion dollars to protect and expand affordable housing in the region, according to an announcement on Thursday. A central player in the project is the philanthropy founded by Facebook’s chief executive, Mark Zuckerberg, and his wife, Dr. Priscilla Chan.

headline.main: $500 Million Pledge in Bay Area Supports Affordable Housing

docs.abstract: In an opinion column, Abigail Disney railed against what she calls the “naked indecency’’ of the practices. Disney disputed her assertions.
docs.snippet: In an opinion column, Abigail Disney railed against what she calls the “naked indecency’’ of the practices. Disney disputed her assertions.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The heiress Abigail Disney made headlines on Monday after she harshly criticized the company founded by her great-uncle on Twitter. On Tuesday she escalated her attack, writing in an opinion column about what she called the “naked indecency” of the company’s pay practices.

headline.main: Disney Heiress Escalates Attack on Company’s Pay Practices
headline.print_headline: Disney Heiress Jabs Harder at Company’s Pay Scale
